# TradeRaider Project Roadmap — Updated
Phase 1: Signal Dashboard & Backend API (DONE)

Built FastAPI backend with /webhook (POST) and /latest_signal (GET) endpoints

Developed frontend dashboard hosted on GitHub Pages to display live signals

Connected frontend with backend via fetch API for real-time updates

Deployed backend on Render.com

Handled CORS and deployment issues

Phase 2: Signal Generation & Sending

Current focus:

Build Python MT5 signal sender script

Connects to MT5 desktop via Python API

Implements your trading strategy logic to generate signals

Sends signals to backend webhook

Testing script locally and on a server/VPS

Phase 3: Deployment & Automation

Set up GitHub repo for Python signal sender code

Automate deployment with GitHub Actions or CI/CD pipeline

Deploy signal sender script on VPS or cloud instance

Ensure 24/7 operation and reliability

Phase 4: Enhancements & White-labeling

Add authentication & security (e.g., HMAC signing for webhook)

Add multi-symbol and multi-strategy support

Integrate more data sources (MT5, TradingView, others)

Build broker white-label API/license model

UI/UX improvements and branding polish

Phase 5: Optional — Advanced Features

Develop a full trading bot with order execution

Add notifications (email, SMS, push) for signals

Add analytics and reporting dashboard

Expand to mobile apps or desktop clients

Next Steps When You’re Ready

Create and push Python MT5 signal sender script to GitHub

Test signal sender locally, connecting MT5 with backend webhook

Deploy signal sender to VPS or cloud

Connect dashboard & backend fully for live signals from MT5

Iterate on strategy and UI based on feedback
